clusterList.phrase: save money on life insurance at the same rate they die young

given that smokers die early saving the rest of society a considerable sum in pension and old-age care costs it is far from clear that the current high rate of tobacco duty can be justified on the grounds of the external costs of smoking but given people's lack of self-control and tendency to take decisions today that they will regret tomorrow high rates of tobacco duty may be appropriate to help protect people from the consequences of their own decisions
